      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANYA HANDLE IT (3) had the drop on the lead before drawing clear to score (29.70) at this track in a Grade 5 over 520m. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Form reads well for this. SPRING WITNESS (7) beaten last start over the 520m at this track but finished in the minors in a swift 29.78. This tougher but expected to be in the finish. BILLY RAY'S GIRL (8) missed the frame last time when sixth (29.99) at Richmond but prior to that had three placings in a row. Solid record at the distance winning seven races. Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break from out wide. Key player if finds best. LOCO BOOM (6) must be respected at his pet distance.",
